Package: gq
Version: 0.6.0
Revision: 1
Depends: openldap-ssl, openssl-shlibs, gtk+-shlibs
BuildDepends: openssl-dev, gtk+, openldap-ssl-dev, db4, glib, readline
Patch: %f.patch
Source: mirror:sourceforge:gqclient/%n-%v.tar.gz
ConfigureParams: --with-gtk-prefix=%p --with-ldap-prefix=%p --with-ssl-prefix=%p --with-kerberos-prefix=/usr
SetCPPFLAGS: -no-cpp-precomp
UpdateConfigGuess: true
UpdateLibtool: true
InstallScript: <<
  make install DESTDIR=%d
<<
DocFiles: AUTHORS COPYING ChangeLog INSTALL NEWS README TODO
Description: GTK+ LDAP Client
DescDetail: <<
GQ is a GTK-based LDAP client.

Features include

    - LDAP browser
    - LDAP V3 Schema browser
    - Template builder
    - Export subtree or whole server to LDIF
    - Use any number of servers
    - Search based on single argument or LDAP filter
    - Edit and delete entries
    - Add entries using an existing entry, or based on your own template
<<
DescPackaging: <<
Only a very small patch was required because of indirect linking
<<
